Community boundaries and familial similarities
[familial similarity] "All the individual x's in the group S have no features in common, but are only loosely connected as a whole by features that are partially common."

Communities and organizations without clear boundaries may be in this state.
There are no common characteristics among the members of that community or organization.

In groups where [initiation rituals] and other rituals exist, "having gone through those rituals" is a common characteristic.
Many people think that "are you employed by that company" is a common trait in traditional companies.
(because in reality there are people involved in many different ways, such as contracting, delegating, owning, etc., but they don't get enough attention)